definitions.definition: A course of action to be followed regularly ; a standard procedure .
A set of normal procedures, often performed mechanically .
examples: Connie was completely robotic and emotionless by age 12; her entire life had become one big routine .

definitions.definition: A set piece of an entertainer 's act .
A set of instructions designed to perform a specific task ; a subroutine .
